    <H3>Program Objectives</H3>
	 <p>
            To provide education support to children in high-risk in different schools of Nicaragua using best psychological practices.
	</p>
	
 <br>
    <H3>Program Presentation</H3>
	<p>
            On the day after arrival, the seminar starts at 3 pm in the Hotel auditorium and ends around 4: 30 pm. During the Presentation, 
            the volunteers will learn about the culture of Nicaragua and the schools where they will be working. They will also receive an 
            explanation of the activities Schedule for the trip.
	</p>
	<br>
       <H3>Hands-On Training</H3>
   	<p>
            Participants will arrive to the school at 8 am, be introduced to the school staff members, and then be divided into groups to 
            participate in the various activities scheduled for each day. The volunteers will have lunch at 12 pm before re-commencing 
            activities at 1 pm. The workday ends at 4 pm.
    </p>
  
	<br>
    <H3>Cultural Tour Day</H3>
    <p>As a break between the 2 weeks of work, students will get a full weekend of fun activities including a visit to the Little Islands 
        of Granada, Old Market Masaya, Masaya’s beautiful Apoyo Lagoon, the Catarina lookout, and a visit to Masaya’s live volcano. 
        The activities will be distributed between a two-day tour.
        </p>
    <p>*Activities are subject to change depending on weather and environmental factors.</p>
    <p>
    While Synaptic Communities will provide transportation, the rest of the expenses (entrance fees and food) will be assumed by the 
    participants.
    </p>
